The new subtitled The Run has produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be during which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set pulls down due to a few unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to settle them begins to participate in illegal races throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The itinerary is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race is done on a different route and the stages planned in different environments that differ quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also quite nice even though the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
The events are in addition from time to time adorned with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly decreases your visibility.
Then in the mountains you need to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the timer) and then another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police that comes into the game and tries to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
It’s more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help them by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing too complicated.
What’s surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete, there are only three).
The result is like this because this element is not likely to be disturbed and, in the context described above, is placed in the elements that adorn the game.
The model of driving is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is nothing extraordinary at the moment, but it cannot be said to be negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of racing design.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, that of collisions is not yet in place.
We don’t expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you don’t have, in a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it’s not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other lightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy volts.
Or it gets in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The reboot is done in such a way that when you have broken your figure or you have gone out into the scenery the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 reboots.
When you have used all 5 restarts you must restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes reboots do not help and you need to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of itinerary in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions are in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that you have to pass in a certain way, otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given location "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
