Students of velvet in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes that takes place with free entrance on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Student of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University take place.
The aim of Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Students’ Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Cheers in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers in addition to high-level concerts, weekly meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Interested parties will find all information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
