Replacing analog signals with digital ones is one of the most important changes the world has suffered in recent years.
The Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) has overturned the constitutional controversies that the Senate and House of Representatives have formulated against the presidential decree advancing the so-called "analog cut" from 2021 to 2015, as the eight votes necessary to invalidate it have not been collected.
