In addition, he hears that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the safe-conduct that allows architects to enter the debate, but "doubts" whether this technical profile should lead the multidisciplinary teams ("everything a success", he says) that one had to create: "We, the architects, should only be an instrument".
Bayona insinuates that the answer to the question that gives the title of this piece is complex, because from the basis of the competition there is a global vision of Collserola: "16 cross-country competitions have been called - he says - in the mountain-sea direction, but there is no longitudinal reading that sees and understands the area as a whole".
This means, at least in this case, that he opted to participate in the 16 competitions.
In another way, a project so that one of the doors can clash in the program and definition with that of the architect of the neighboring door.
In its opinion, yes, the town hall should ensure that the immediately higher band than that of Ronda de Dalt should provide, in its entirety, an area of equipment that makes a smooth transition between the city and the green.
