So was the work of the person from Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali typist has gone down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is crucial.
On November 4, a fingerprint scanner from Cali’s CTI went down in history as the person who confirmed the identity of the FARC Supreme Leader: “Alfonso Cano,” by confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven fingerprint scanners working in the ITC’s local offices, this week it was the “availability” turn of Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, a Puerto Tejada man who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez worked in the municipalities of Choc<0xC3><0xB3>, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he moved to the capital of Valle and after taking appropriate courses, he specialized in typing, which is the study of friction skin, i.e., palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be that of the man who was leading the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo Le<0xC3><0xB3>n S<0xC3><0xA1>enz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the location of the body, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, because this one was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much leaner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a pickup and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the official who confirmed to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinz<0xC3><0xB3>n that yes, he was the supreme leader of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a Sij<0xC3><0xAD>n de Cali typist, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez in a press conference for the operation against "Cano" is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know our work.
Fingerprinting is an accurate science, with no margin for error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
In addition to identifying the bodies, fingerprint scanners support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of those captured.
When caught, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove part of the wall of a house, because in this place the thief had held his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to take a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different flights," he recalls.
Footprints can also discard or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently, a dead man was found, with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a parent may be suspected of the crime and indeed a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if that doesn't guarantee he's the killer, it puts him on the scene.
A CTI typist explained that “fingerprints are extracted from objects with chemical or physical reagents.”
When they appear, a pickup or strip is used to pick them up.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the delinquents database, or the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still a lot of undocumented Colombians,” the ITC expert said.
He explained that not everything is how it is shown in the CSI television program.
Since everything that shines is not gold, everything that is touched does not necessarily become an imprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
